                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51 W 89 Czechoslovakia/13</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Czechoslovak Legation</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p>The Legation of the Czechoslovak Republic presents its compliments to The
                    Honorable, The Secretary of State, and has the honor to inform that the Minister
                    of Foreign Affairs of the Czechoslovak Republic has, for the period of the
                    temporary absence of the Czechoslovak Minister to the United States, Dr. Bedfich
                    Stepanek named Dr. Alois Štangler, Counsellor of the Czechoslovak Legation in
                    Washington, D. C., the representative of the Government of the Czechoslovak
                    Republic in every eventual action of the United States Government in connection
                    with the debts of the Czechoslovak Republic to the United States in the Foreign
                    Debt Commission in the United States.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-07-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 8, 1922</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
